    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-11-14T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-11-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/4028: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Ceiba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Evans</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ceiba</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-11-14T09:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1926—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Department’s telegram of November 10, 6 p.m., received November 13,
                    9 a.m. The Governor published his statement in the only newspaper appearing last
                    evening and informs me that publication will be made in all the local press. He
                    states that the military authorities proceeded yesterday to take steps to
                    inflict disciplinary punishment upon the <hi rend="italic">mayor de plaza</hi>
                    who will cease to exercise his functions on November 15th. Will report further
                    by cable. Repeated to Legation at Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Evans</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
